Senate Chief whip, Senator Orji Uzor Kalu has been declared the winner of Abia North senatorial district by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). Kalu of the All Progressive Congress (APC) was declared winner by the INEC returning Officer for Abia North, Mr Chinedu Nnamdi at Ohafia. Kalu, according to the Returning Officer, scored 30,805 votes to defeat Nnamdi Iroh of Labour Party who got 27,540 votes. Kalu’s arch rival, Senator Mao Ohuabunwa of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) scored 15,175 votes to place second. In his brief thank you message, Senator Orji Uzor Kalu thanked the people of Abia North for re-election him as their Senator. Similarly, Hon Benjamin of the APC has defeated Hon Nnenna Ukeje and candidates of other political parties to win the Bende Federal Constituency seat for the second term. Benjamin Kalu who is the Spokesman of the Federal House of Representatives, scaled all odds by scoring 10,20 votes to win a return to the green Chamber. The candidate of Labour Party, Chief Frank Chinaza came second with 6,818 votes while Ben Kalu’s arch rival, Hon Elendu Nnenna Ukeje of the PDP scored only 3,930 votes. The results were announced by the INEC Returning Officer, Chidinma Adindu.